The paper proposes a set of design patterns for systems that combine statistical techniques from machine learning with symbolic techniques from knowledge representation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the systematization of literature and re-use of software components, which are topics related to Software Engineering (cs.SE). The use of knowledge representation techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the Knowledge Representation and Reasoning (cs.KR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the combination of different techniques to create hybrid systems, which is a topic related to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
